payload: ---------------------- Forwarded by Irena D Hogan/HOU/ECT on 06/13/2000 08:31 AM --------------------------- Brent A Price 06/13/2000 07:59 AM To: Irena D Hogan/HOU/ECT@ECT cc: Subject: Officializing Risk Books Irena - Please forward to all in Risk Management: In the last few weeks there have been numerous occasions in which certain risk books have not been officialized. Most of these instances have been due to oversight; one instance was at the direction of Commercial. I want to re-emphasise the importance of ensuring that all risk books are officialized at the end of the day. This is the only mechanism we have to ensure that all trading positions are included in the Daily Position Report and daily trading limit calculations, both of which are reviewed by top Enron management on a daily basis. This must be a top priority for Risk Management and we need to do whatever we have to do to make sure we remember to perform this function at the end of every day. Furthermore, it is totally unacceptable for Commercial to direct any book administrator to not officialize a risk book. If this occurs again and you are uncomfortable with dealing with the situation, please inform your Desk Controller, Steve Jackson or myself immediately and we will address the issue. I realise every one of you has a lot on your plate and are working significant hours to get your jobs done. However, let's do what we have to do to make sure that this basic responsibility of Risk Management is performed every day without any exceptions. Brent

Thank you ---------------------- Forwarded by Irena D Hogan/HOU/ECT on 12/07/2000 10:58 AM --------------------------- Jeffrey C Gossett 12/07/2000 10:24 AM To: Kam Keiser/HOU/ECT@ECT, Darron C Giron/HOU/ECT@ECT, William Kelly/HOU/ECT@ECT, David Baumbach/HOU/ECT@ECT, Errol McLaughlin/Corp/Enron@ENRON cc: Irena D Hogan/HOU/ECT@ECT, Elizabeth Soto/HOU/ECT@ECT Subject: 8:30 Meeting on systems There is a 30 minute meeting every morning on the 28th floor at 8:30 about systems issues from the prior night and to discuss what books were not officialized. Week of : Dec. 4 - Jeff Gossett Dec. 11 - Darron Giron Dec. 18 - David Baumbach Dec. 25 - Will Kelly Jan. 1 - Kam Keiser Jan. 8 - Errol Mclaughlin And then we will start over again. If you can not go, make sure that someone goes in your place. Thanks Irena and Elizabeth - Can you please add these daily meetings to the appropriate calender? Thanks

payload: ---------------------- Forwarded by Irena D Hogan/HOU/ECT on 06/13/2000 08:31 AM --------------------------- Brent A Price 06/13/2000 07:59 AM To: Irena D Hogan/HOU/ECT@ECT cc: Subject: Officializing Risk Books Irena - Please forward to all in Risk Management: In the last few weeks there have been numerous occasions in which certain risk books have not been officialized. Most of these instances have been due to oversight; one instance was at the direction of Commercial. I want to re-emphasise the importance of ensuring that all risk books are officialized at the end of the day. This is the only mechanism we have to ensure that all trading positions are included in the Daily Position Report and daily trading limit calculations, both of which are reviewed by top Enron management on a daily basis. This must be a top priority for Risk Management and we need to do whatever we have to do to make sure we remember to perform this function at the end of every day. Furthermore, it is totally unacceptable for Commercial to direct any book administrator to not officialize a risk book. If this occurs again and you are uncomfortable with dealing with the situation, please inform your Desk Controller, Steve Jackson or myself immediately and we will address the issue. I realise every one of you has a lot on your plate and are working significant hours to get your jobs done. However, let's do what we have to do to make sure that this basic responsibility of Risk Management is performed every day without any exceptions. Brent
